## Summary

Added a Hugging Face ("Hugg") adapter for **Model** search, treating Model as a first-class component type alongside skill/agent/prompt/mcp.

**Approach (RGR):** Wrote `huggingface.test.ts` first (8 cases covering enablement, type gating, endpoint/query, auth header, result mapping, id filtering, non-array bodies, and error status), then the implementation to pass them.

**Key changes:**
- `src/lib/adapters/types.ts` — new `'model'` `ComponentType` and `'huggingface'` `AdapterId`.
- `src/lib/adapters/huggingface.ts` — follows the skillsmp shape: `supports()` gated to `'model'` only, `isEnabled()` always true (public API), optional `HUGGINGFACE_API_TOKEN` bearer. Calls `GET /api/models?search=…&limit=10&sort=likes&direction=-1`, maps entries to `{title:id, url:huggingface.co/<id>, description:pipeline_tag, stars:likes}`, filters ids and tolerates a non-array body.
- Wired into `createAdapters`, `config`, `rank.ts` (weight 3), the `/api/search` zod enum, the `SearchForm` dropdown, and homepage copy.

**Verification:** `npm run typecheck` clean; `npm run test` 53/53 green. Committed as `f9ed46e` on `sandcastle/issue-2`, and left a progress comment on issue #2 (not closed).

